1
00:00:14,986 --> 00:00:16,096
Mom...

2
00:00:17,342 --> 00:00:18,832
How is Ms. Weiling doing?

3
00:00:25,122 --> 00:00:27,332
I have cardiomyopathy,

4
00:00:28,622 --> 00:00:29,682
probably from all the drinking

5
00:00:30,432 --> 00:00:32,022
after what happened back then.

6
00:00:33,212 --> 00:00:34,582
But I've never told Lalin.

7
00:00:35,332 --> 00:00:36,532
I didn't want to worry her.

8
00:00:38,342 --> 00:00:39,932
She ends up like this because of me.

9
00:00:43,102 --> 00:00:44,102
Don't blame yourself.

10
00:00:44,842 --> 00:00:46,202
You're here with me right now.

11
00:00:50,842 --> 00:00:52,812
Isn't Lalin with you?

12
00:00:55,642 --> 00:00:57,252
I was going to ask

13
00:00:59,502 --> 00:01:00,502
where she is.

14
00:01:01,392 --> 00:01:03,052
She left before I did, didn't she?

15
00:01:11,412 --> 00:01:12,142
Wit...

16
00:01:15,142 --> 00:01:16,222
Lalin!

17
00:01:16,752 --> 00:01:18,572
Where are you? Who did this to you?

18
00:01:19,262 --> 00:01:20,202
Wit! Lalin!

19
00:01:20,522 --> 00:01:21,492
What is this?

20
00:01:21,682 --> 00:01:22,932
Why are you holding my daughter captive?

21
00:01:23,272 --> 00:01:24,612
Ms. Weiling, this has nothing to do with you.

22
00:01:25,142 --> 00:01:27,262
Arisa is the one who started all of this.

23
00:01:27,522 --> 00:01:29,272
If she hadn't messed with my wife,

24
00:01:29,442 --> 00:01:31,202
Ms. Lalin wouldn't have to be here now.

25
00:01:31,542 --> 00:01:32,412
Arisa,

26
00:01:32,732 --> 00:01:33,732
where the hell did you take Pin to?

27
00:01:33,782 --> 00:01:34,892
Calm down.

28
00:01:35,422 --> 00:01:36,422
Listen to me.

29
00:01:36,682 --> 00:01:38,082
Just let Pin go.

30
00:01:38,622 --> 00:01:39,682
Please, trust me.

31
00:01:39,762 --> 00:01:40,342
Wit,

32
00:01:41,432 --> 00:01:42,532
let's talk it out.

33
00:01:43,432 --> 00:01:44,492
What do you want?

34
00:01:44,602 --> 00:01:46,412
Just return my wife to me,

35
00:01:46,602 --> 00:01:47,882
and everything will be over!

36
00:01:48,582 --> 00:01:51,442
If you don't bring Pin to me by tonight,

37
00:01:54,082 --> 00:01:55,342
there's no reason

38
00:01:55,862 --> 00:01:56,982
for me to let Ms. Lalin live.

39
00:01:57,122 --> 00:01:59,492
Wit, calm down.

40
00:01:59,732 --> 00:02:00,612
I'm begging you.

41
00:02:00,882 --> 00:02:02,732
Just do as I ask,

42
00:02:03,492 --> 00:02:05,092
and don't bring any cops with you;

43
00:02:05,422 --> 00:02:07,812
otherwise, Ms. Lalin is as good as dead!

44
00:02:08,062 --> 00:02:08,602
Wit!

45
00:02:08,642 --> 00:02:09,932
Wit, don't! Wit!

46
00:02:09,972 --> 00:02:10,892
Easy!

47
00:02:10,922 --> 00:02:11,742
Let go of me!

48
00:02:11,772 --> 00:02:12,622
Where are you going?!

49
00:02:12,652 --> 00:02:14,612
- I'm going to help my daughter! - You can't!

50
00:02:14,652 --> 00:02:15,572
You're still not well.

51
00:02:15,602 --> 00:02:17,462
How can you go now? What if it flares up?!

52
00:02:17,822 --> 00:02:18,612
Ms. Weiling!

53
00:02:20,022 --> 00:02:21,512
All of this

54
00:02:21,932 --> 00:02:23,242
happened because of me,

55
00:02:24,042 --> 00:02:26,012
because of how desperate I was.

56
00:02:26,952 --> 00:02:28,372
If I hadn't agitated him

57
00:02:28,942 --> 00:02:30,632
because I wanted to beat you,

58
00:02:31,022 --> 00:02:33,302
Lalin wouldn't have ended up like this.

59
00:02:34,412 --> 00:02:36,182
It started with me,

60
00:02:36,332 --> 00:02:37,942
so it has to end with me.

61
00:02:43,512 --> 00:02:44,942
Isn't this too risky?

62
00:02:45,252 --> 00:02:46,922
Shouldn't we let the police handle this?

63
00:02:47,912 --> 00:02:50,762
I won't let anyone lay a hand on the person I love.

64
00:02:50,862 --> 00:02:52,362
Don't worry, Mom.

65
00:02:55,862 --> 00:02:57,792
You have to be really careful, sweetheart.

66
00:02:58,932 --> 00:03:01,122
I can't lose you, either.

67
00:03:02,722 --> 00:03:03,592
Alright.

68
00:03:07,812 --> 00:03:08,882
I'm leaving it to you.

69
00:03:17,872 --> 00:03:18,532
Aiy,

70
00:03:18,932 --> 00:03:20,072
I'm on my way to help Lalin.

71
00:03:20,352 --> 00:03:21,452
What do you mean?

72
00:03:21,622 --> 00:03:22,622
What happened, Boss?

73
00:03:22,662 --> 00:03:24,522
Wit is holding her captive.

74
00:03:24,562 --> 00:03:26,002
Are you gonna go there by yourself?

75
00:03:26,042 --> 00:03:27,582
Please let me come with you, Boss.

76
00:04:22,302 --> 00:04:24,072
Please let me go.

77
00:04:24,342 --> 00:04:25,202
Hey!

78
00:04:25,602 --> 00:04:27,782
Please let me go, Wit.

79
00:04:28,602 --> 00:04:29,602
Wit...

80
00:04:30,312 --> 00:04:32,642
Can we just talk things over?

81
00:04:32,682 --> 00:04:33,772
Wit!

82
00:04:38,352 --> 00:04:40,542
Wit, please take it off me.

83
00:04:40,582 --> 00:04:42,402
Please don't do this.

84
00:04:48,262 --> 00:04:49,262
Wit,

85
00:04:51,012 --> 00:04:54,492
this is not going to help with anything.

86
00:04:56,392 --> 00:04:57,762
Even with this,

87
00:04:58,062 --> 00:05:00,302
Ms. Pin is not coming back to you.

88
00:05:04,122 --> 00:05:04,812
Ms. Lalin,

89
00:05:07,532 --> 00:05:08,502
you wouldn't understand.

90
00:05:10,122 --> 00:05:11,922
Pin and I have been together for more than ten years.

91
00:05:13,412 --> 00:05:14,412
Everything I've done,

92
00:05:15,252 --> 00:05:16,942
all the work I did was for her!

93
00:05:19,972 --> 00:05:22,242
No matter what, she loves me, and she's going to come back!

94
00:05:22,342 --> 00:05:24,932
That's not love, Wit.

95
00:05:27,052 --> 00:05:28,482
You just hold onto her

96
00:05:28,512 --> 00:05:31,252
to reassure yourself that you still have someone in your life.

97
00:05:32,432 --> 00:05:33,092
Wit,

98
00:05:33,422 --> 00:05:34,322
believe me.

99
00:05:34,362 --> 00:05:35,282
Don't do this.

100
00:05:35,542 --> 00:05:37,122
It won't make anything better.

101
00:05:37,502 --> 00:05:38,542
Please let me go.

102
00:05:38,572 --> 00:05:39,312
- No. - Don't...

103
00:05:39,352 --> 00:05:40,432
Please don't do this.

104
00:05:40,462 --> 00:05:41,412
You wouldn't understand!

105
00:05:43,342 --> 00:05:44,812
What I did

106
00:05:46,912 --> 00:05:47,992
was out of love.

107
00:05:49,652 --> 00:05:51,342
And it all fell apart

108
00:05:51,552 --> 00:05:52,812
because of Arisa!

109
00:06:09,052 --> 00:06:10,412
Don't do this...

110
00:06:11,622 --> 00:06:12,892
Please let me go...

111
00:06:56,592 --> 00:06:57,322
Pin...

112
00:07:21,122 --> 00:07:21,812
Pin...

113
00:07:33,462 --> 00:07:34,932
Arisa!

114
00:07:37,282 --> 00:07:37,852
Whoa!

115
00:07:39,432 --> 00:07:41,252
Please help!

116
00:07:41,462 --> 00:07:42,222
Help...

117
00:07:43,652 --> 00:07:44,412
Aiy, go!

118
00:07:44,762 --> 00:07:45,432
Hey!

119
00:07:47,392 --> 00:07:49,562
Please! Help me!

120
00:07:55,612 --> 00:07:56,252
Ms. Lalin...

121
00:07:56,292 --> 00:07:57,622
- Ms. Aiy... - Are you alright?

122
00:07:57,652 --> 00:07:58,612
Are you alright?

123
00:07:58,942 --> 00:07:59,942
Hold on just a second.

124
00:08:10,872 --> 00:08:12,422
Okay, okay...

125
00:08:13,902 --> 00:08:14,902
Just a second.

126
00:08:19,152 --> 00:08:20,172
Come on.

127
00:08:46,912 --> 00:08:47,612
Ow...

128
00:09:06,742 --> 00:09:08,082
Give Pin back to me.

129
00:09:08,112 --> 00:09:10,962
Pin would never stay with a monster like you!

130
00:09:11,512 --> 00:09:13,022
How could you do this to Lalin?

131
00:09:13,152 --> 00:09:14,152
How could you?!

132
00:09:14,352 --> 00:09:15,152
No!!

133
00:09:15,202 --> 00:09:17,052
Give my Pin back to me!

134
00:10:05,132 --> 00:10:07,182
This is where Ms. Lalin is being held captive.

135
00:10:07,382 --> 00:10:09,072
All right, we will spread out and search.

136
00:10:09,282 --> 00:10:11,502
Two to the left, two to the rear, and two to the front. Go!

137
00:10:25,222 --> 00:10:25,722
This way.

138
00:10:26,762 --> 00:10:27,332
Come on.

139
00:11:01,002 --> 00:11:01,832
Officer,

140
00:11:01,942 --> 00:11:03,172
the guy went that way.

141
00:11:03,942 --> 00:11:04,782
Copy!

142
00:11:05,202 --> 00:11:06,202
Are you okay?

143
00:11:07,032 --> 00:11:08,092
Breathe slowly.

144
00:11:08,302 --> 00:11:09,882
You're safe now.

145
00:11:12,182 --> 00:11:13,122
Take it easy.

146
00:11:14,052 --> 00:11:15,232
Breathe slowly.

147
00:11:16,362 --> 00:11:17,622
You're okay now.

148
00:11:23,822 --> 00:11:25,302
- Ow... - Hey, are you holding up okay?

149
00:11:25,822 --> 00:11:27,522
Take it easy. Easy.

150
00:11:28,152 --> 00:11:29,152
You can push through, right?

151
00:11:29,662 --> 00:11:30,512
Okay.

152
00:11:32,922 --> 00:11:33,622
Come here!

153
00:11:33,652 --> 00:11:34,412
Hey!

154
00:11:35,502 --> 00:11:36,082
Let go of me!

155
00:11:36,432 --> 00:11:37,342
- Let go of me! - Stop!

156
00:11:37,382 --> 00:11:38,672
- Wit! - Stop!

157
00:11:40,512 --> 00:11:42,032
Lalin has nothing to do with this.

158
00:11:43,152 --> 00:11:45,092
She has nothing to do with this at all.

159
00:11:45,232 --> 00:11:46,192
Let her go.

160
00:11:46,222 --> 00:11:47,182
I surrender.

161
00:11:48,142 --> 00:11:49,752
To everything.

162
00:11:49,912 --> 00:11:51,232
Don't tell me what to do.

163
00:11:52,702 --> 00:11:54,412
You took Pin away from me.

164
00:11:55,492 --> 00:11:56,862
I'll take Lalin from you, too!

165
00:11:56,892 --> 00:11:58,782
Don't! Don't! Don't! Don't....

166
00:11:59,172 --> 00:12:00,022
Don't!

167
00:12:01,492 --> 00:12:02,562
Calm down.

168
00:12:03,122 --> 00:12:04,122
Just calm down.

169
00:12:05,002 --> 00:12:06,682
We can talk it out, Wit.

170
00:12:08,092 --> 00:12:09,002
I really am surrendering.

171
00:12:09,032 --> 00:12:10,072
I'm not listening to your bulls*it anymore!

172
00:12:11,162 --> 00:12:12,332
No matter what,

173
00:12:12,522 --> 00:12:14,552
you both will f*cking die today!

174
00:12:14,592 --> 00:12:15,662
Stop! Stop! Stop...

175
00:12:15,702 --> 00:12:16,362
- Enough... - Stop!

176
00:12:19,512 --> 00:12:20,452
Put the gun down, now!

177
00:12:22,102 --> 00:12:22,902
I said, drop the gun!

178
00:12:33,812 --> 00:12:34,812
Arisa...

179
00:12:37,352 --> 00:12:38,662
You tricked me!

180
00:12:52,432 --> 00:12:53,432
Uncle Mek!

181
00:12:56,952 --> 00:12:57,952
Argh!

182
00:13:02,602 --> 00:13:03,532
Uncle!

183
00:13:03,972 --> 00:13:06,292
I told you I didn't want to see your face anymore!

184
00:13:06,472 --> 00:13:08,372
Why did you come here?!

185
00:13:11,142 --> 00:13:12,012
Why did you...

186
00:13:17,712 --> 00:13:21,522
I promised your father...

187
00:13:23,632 --> 00:13:26,522
that I would take good care of you.

188
00:13:31,402 --> 00:13:32,482
I...

189
00:13:35,492 --> 00:13:37,652
I've fulfilled my promise at last.

190
00:13:46,262 --> 00:13:47,322
Uncle Mek...

191
00:13:47,492 --> 00:13:48,412
Uncle Mek!

192
00:13:48,632 --> 00:13:49,932
Uncle Mek!

193
00:13:56,522 --> 00:13:57,682
Uncle Mek...

194
00:14:13,642 --> 00:14:16,242
I solemnly forgive you for everything you did,

195
00:14:17,132 --> 00:14:20,812
and thank you for taking care of Kee for me.

196
00:14:28,512 --> 00:14:30,452
Thank you, Uncle,

197
00:14:34,832 --> 00:14:38,392
for protecting me throughout my life,

198
00:14:42,222 --> 00:14:44,542
even until your last breath.

199
00:15:06,662 --> 00:15:08,832
It's all over now, sweetheart.

200
00:15:14,102 --> 00:15:16,412
If you want to cry,

201
00:15:17,422 --> 00:15:18,902
let it all out,

202
00:15:22,442 --> 00:15:24,142
and from now on,

203
00:15:25,532 --> 00:15:27,972
only good things will come our way.

204
00:15:58,512 --> 00:16:00,132
Even though he's passed,

205
00:16:00,272 --> 00:16:02,322
he's still guilty.

206
00:16:05,272 --> 00:16:07,462
Don't live your life in vindictiveness.

207
00:16:08,002 --> 00:16:10,252
I've seen enough people suffer because of it.

208
00:16:11,802 --> 00:16:14,602
It's best... to live in the present.

209
00:16:17,142 --> 00:16:18,832
I didn't mean anything by it.

210
00:16:19,632 --> 00:16:21,062
I'm just relieved

211
00:16:21,332 --> 00:16:22,882
to know who was behind what happened to my dad.

212
00:16:25,882 --> 00:16:27,732
I've forgiven him now.

213
00:16:29,622 --> 00:16:30,622
That's good.

214
00:16:31,062 --> 00:16:34,602
Nevertheless, I'm sorry about your dad.

215
00:16:35,602 --> 00:16:37,052
You turn out to be so amazing.

216
00:16:37,382 --> 00:16:40,732
Your dad must be proud of you somewhere.

217
00:16:42,802 --> 00:16:43,902
Thank you.

218
00:16:45,302 --> 00:16:46,922
At least, there's something good

219
00:16:47,512 --> 00:16:49,372
coming out of this.

220
00:16:51,502 --> 00:16:52,502
Which part?

221
00:16:55,392 --> 00:16:57,202
The part where I met you.

222
00:17:05,622 --> 00:17:06,622
Right,

223
00:17:07,482 --> 00:17:09,692
despite what you give off, you're pretty brave.

224
00:17:11,242 --> 00:17:14,422
You know how much danger you put yourself through, right?

225
00:17:16,162 --> 00:17:17,152
Yes,

226
00:17:17,972 --> 00:17:19,782
I do know it was dangerous.

227
00:17:19,812 --> 00:17:23,032
Actually, my boss wouldn't let me come,

228
00:17:25,022 --> 00:17:27,642
but I really couldn't let her be there alone.

229
00:17:30,412 --> 00:17:33,002
Then, can I ask you something?

230
00:17:34,422 --> 00:17:37,952
That day, were you really just there to cover the news?

231
00:17:42,942 --> 00:17:44,572
I wasn't there for coverage.

232
00:17:45,642 --> 00:17:46,982
I went there to help you.

233
00:17:52,742 --> 00:17:53,742
Thank you.

234
00:17:57,822 --> 00:17:58,672
Come on.

235
00:18:24,948 --> 00:18:26,818
Everything went smoothly.

236
00:18:27,378 --> 00:18:29,328
She can probably be discharged by this evening.

237
00:18:29,818 --> 00:18:33,638
All that's left is to make sure the patient take all her medications.

238
00:18:34,298 --> 00:18:35,878
And more importantly,

239
00:18:35,958 --> 00:18:37,438
she must avoid drinking entirely

240
00:18:37,898 --> 00:18:42,918
and you all must warn her not to exert herself too much;

241
00:18:43,648 --> 00:18:46,408
or else there could be a relapse.

242
00:18:48,318 --> 00:18:49,858
Thank you so much, Doctor.

243
00:18:49,958 --> 00:18:50,958
Excuse me.

244
00:18:59,308 --> 00:19:00,308
Mom,

245
00:19:00,768 --> 00:19:03,678
why have you never told me that you were this sick?

246
00:19:05,008 --> 00:19:07,308
Ever since I asked you to come home,

247
00:19:08,378 --> 00:19:10,198
I've always been prepared.

248
00:19:12,418 --> 00:19:13,418
You really don't know...

249
00:19:13,758 --> 00:19:15,008
if you'll get to live another day, right?

250
00:19:16,758 --> 00:19:19,428
Nevertheless, I still wanted to witness you becoming ready...

251
00:19:19,448 --> 00:19:21,528
to mature, and to take care of yourself

252
00:19:21,608 --> 00:19:23,778
and what I've built.

253
00:19:25,628 --> 00:19:26,628
There it is.

254
00:19:27,428 --> 00:19:28,428
Look at you.

255
00:19:28,758 --> 00:19:30,598
You're as stubborn as I am!

256
00:19:30,928 --> 00:19:32,548
You assumed things

257
00:19:32,618 --> 00:19:34,198
and planned everything out by yourself.

258
00:19:34,888 --> 00:19:36,808
You didn't even think about my feelings at all.

259
00:19:38,708 --> 00:19:39,708
I'm sorry.

260
00:19:41,828 --> 00:19:44,118
If you want me to forgive you,

261
00:19:44,178 --> 00:19:46,608
you've got to be a good patient.

262
00:19:47,878 --> 00:19:49,058
From now on,

263
00:19:49,128 --> 00:19:50,768
I'll be the one taking care of you.

264
00:19:52,518 --> 00:19:54,358
Could I help you with that, too?

265
00:19:56,328 --> 00:19:58,058
I need to take responsibility as well.

266
00:20:03,128 --> 00:20:05,338
If you want to take care of me out of guilt,

267
00:20:06,198 --> 00:20:07,198
don't.

268
00:20:09,828 --> 00:20:12,278
But if you want to, because you care,

269
00:20:13,898 --> 00:20:15,178
I can oblige.

270
00:20:22,468 --> 00:20:24,258
It's probably for the best with how things turned out.

271
00:20:24,828 --> 00:20:26,598
It's given me time to reflect.

272
00:20:27,998 --> 00:20:30,638
After working so hard for half of my life,

273
00:20:30,668 --> 00:20:32,378
I don't even know what it's for.

274
00:20:33,098 --> 00:20:34,618
In the end,

275
00:20:35,558 --> 00:20:37,948
I just want to be with my loved ones.

276
00:21:03,208 --> 00:21:04,338
I...

277
00:21:11,498 --> 00:21:13,318
I want to apologize, Ms. Weiling.

278
00:21:15,528 --> 00:21:17,618
I'm sorry about everything.

279
00:21:20,338 --> 00:21:22,708
I'm sorry that I made you sad.

280
00:21:26,938 --> 00:21:29,128
Could you find it in your heart to forgive me?

281
00:21:57,178 --> 00:21:58,798
You can call me "Mom."

282
00:22:03,468 --> 00:22:04,588
I forgive you.

283
00:22:09,988 --> 00:22:11,088
How could someone...

284
00:22:11,128 --> 00:22:13,518
stay angry at their own family for that long?

285
00:22:16,298 --> 00:22:17,758
From now on,

286
00:22:17,788 --> 00:22:19,838
we shouldn't dwell on the past anymore.

287
00:22:20,888 --> 00:22:23,248
Live for yourself.

288
00:22:24,228 --> 00:22:26,138
And take care of Lalin on my behalf.

289
00:22:33,548 --> 00:22:34,698
Of course.

290
00:23:01,598 --> 00:23:07,768
♫Morning comes with the early summer light♫

291
00:23:11,628 --> 00:23:19,858
♫Curtains sway gently by the window♫

292
00:23:20,238 --> 00:23:26,138
♫And you're sleeping♫

293
00:23:31,478 --> 00:23:38,238
♫Tender wind dancing on my skin♫

294
00:23:41,298 --> 00:23:49,508
♫Makes me stay in bed a little longer♫

295
00:23:49,598 --> 00:23:56,278
♫To hear you breathing♫

296
00:24:01,148 --> 00:24:05,808
♫Long for those quiet days♫

297
00:24:05,868 --> 00:24:10,488
♫Where the hours drift away♫

298
00:24:11,188 --> 00:24:15,708
♫Petals fall on the windowpane♫

299
00:24:15,738 --> 00:24:19,568
♫As the clouds above♫

300
00:24:21,188 --> 00:24:26,498
♫Float away♫

301
00:25:23,568 --> 00:25:25,318
- Wanna wash your hands? - Sure.

302
00:25:25,498 --> 00:25:26,498
Can you pour it for me?

303
00:25:31,458 --> 00:25:32,458
A bit more.

304
00:25:33,698 --> 00:25:34,698
Okay.

305
00:25:41,218 --> 00:25:43,638
Hey! What was that?

306
00:25:49,978 --> 00:25:52,298
I wish to be with you like this for a long time.

307
00:25:52,448 --> 00:25:53,828
Forever, even.

308
00:25:54,898 --> 00:25:56,858
Well, you're right here.

309
00:25:57,818 --> 00:25:58,598
Hm?

310
00:25:59,098 --> 00:26:02,008
But I have to go to work tomorrow...

311
00:26:02,718 --> 00:26:04,008
You don't want to work?

312
00:26:05,708 --> 00:26:07,378
It's not that I don't want to,

313
00:26:07,918 --> 00:26:09,488
but I'm just scared I'd blow it.

314
00:26:10,348 --> 00:26:11,848
I'm scared I'd disappoint my mom.

315
00:26:12,488 --> 00:26:14,298
For once, I want her to take a break.

316
00:26:16,058 --> 00:26:17,398
There's nothing to be scared of.

317
00:26:18,288 --> 00:26:19,738
You're such a fast learner.

318
00:26:19,808 --> 00:26:21,268
You'll get it before you know it.

319
00:26:21,298 --> 00:26:22,978
More importantly,

320
00:26:23,318 --> 00:26:26,528
you have a partner who's both skilled and smart right here.

321
00:26:26,658 --> 00:26:28,008
What's there to be scared of?

322
00:26:29,678 --> 00:26:32,608
There's no need to be scared. You've got this.

323
00:26:33,638 --> 00:26:37,208
Or if you don't come to like it or find happiness in it,

324
00:26:37,618 --> 00:26:39,108
do you want to go back to being Lyla?

325
00:26:41,398 --> 00:26:43,808
Lyla or Lalin,

326
00:26:43,958 --> 00:26:45,778
without you,

327
00:26:45,808 --> 00:26:47,948
I won't find happiness.

328
00:26:48,868 --> 00:26:50,378
Then, I won't, either.

329
00:26:50,688 --> 00:26:52,458
Whether if I'm Keetraphat

330
00:26:52,518 --> 00:26:54,178
or Arisa,

331
00:26:54,438 --> 00:26:56,668
I won't find happiness without you.

332
00:27:17,828 --> 00:27:19,488
This ring

333
00:27:20,128 --> 00:27:22,248
will represent our love,

334
00:27:22,498 --> 00:27:23,978
a token of our promises.

335
00:27:28,218 --> 00:27:30,738
There will be no more grudges from now on.

336
00:27:34,398 --> 00:27:35,388
Yes,

337
00:27:36,078 --> 00:27:38,798
it's going to be a token of our love.

338
00:27:46,028 --> 00:27:53,868
♫I have always been cluless♫

339
00:27:55,078 --> 00:28:00,358
♫Until I met you, my dear♫

340
00:28:00,398 --> 00:28:03,198
From now on, don't ever throw it at me again.

341
00:28:03,268 --> 00:28:04,968
If it happens again,

342
00:28:05,088 --> 00:28:07,198
I won't pick it up for you.

343
00:28:07,288 --> 00:28:09,138
That's gonna teach you a lesson.

344
00:28:11,488 --> 00:28:12,908
It already did.

345
00:28:13,018 --> 00:28:16,148
♫I want to whisper by your ears,♫

346
00:28:16,188 --> 00:28:18,918
I love you.

347
00:28:19,758 --> 00:28:21,428
I love you, too.

348
00:28:23,938 --> 00:28:28,648
♫Hold on to my hands tightly♫

349
00:28:28,678 --> 00:28:33,028
♫Would you be here, right next to me?♫

350
00:28:33,058 --> 00:28:37,538
♫Look at me,tell me honestly♫

351
00:28:37,568 --> 00:28:40,168
♫If you feel as I do♫

352
00:28:43,138 --> 00:28:46,738
Am I the most interesting person in your eyes now?

353
00:28:49,338 --> 00:28:50,588
Hm...

354
00:28:52,058 --> 00:28:53,248
Not yet.

355
00:28:54,508 --> 00:28:56,878
Anything else for me to discover?

356
00:29:00,018 --> 00:29:02,298
There's a lot more to be discovered.

357
00:29:02,988 --> 00:29:05,528
I have a lot of surprises awaiting you.

358
00:29:13,508 --> 00:29:14,668
Try me.

359
00:29:16,078 --> 00:29:17,518
In the car?

360
00:29:19,078 --> 00:29:20,418
What's there to be scared of?

361
00:29:20,958 --> 00:29:23,228
This is your own racetrack.

362
00:29:23,498 --> 00:29:25,298
No one else is gonna be here.

363
00:32:46,975 --> 00:32:48,498
Be sure to read all of these.

364
00:32:51,999 --> 00:32:53,239
That's a mistake.

365
00:32:54,400 --> 00:32:57,159
You need to look at every page thoroughly.

366
00:33:28,223 --> 00:33:30,762
There are different kinds...

367
00:33:43,235 --> 00:33:44,555
It's Friday.

368
00:33:44,825 --> 00:33:46,235
Aren't you going somewhere, Boss?

369
00:33:46,535 --> 00:33:47,765
I don't think so.

370
00:33:47,966 --> 00:33:49,436
Arisa is busy.

371
00:33:50,495 --> 00:33:51,415
What about you?

372
00:33:54,255 --> 00:33:55,595
Well...

373
00:33:55,735 --> 00:33:59,985
I'm thinking about asking a neighbor to join me for dinner.

374
00:34:01,615 --> 00:34:03,095
Oh...

375
00:34:03,995 --> 00:34:05,765
"A neighbor."

376
00:34:09,755 --> 00:34:10,755
Okay.

377
00:34:11,655 --> 00:34:13,265
I'm rooting for you.

378
00:34:13,435 --> 00:34:15,425
What for?

379
00:34:15,465 --> 00:34:17,275
It's just a neighbor.

380
00:34:17,515 --> 00:34:19,185
I have eyes.

381
00:34:20,445 --> 00:34:22,035
Enjoy.

382
00:34:25,895 --> 00:34:26,995
I'd better head out.

383
00:34:27,635 --> 00:34:28,745
Bye-bye.

384
00:34:50,625 --> 00:34:52,325
Did you bathe in cologne?

385
00:34:53,715 --> 00:34:55,155
It's like you're going on a date or something.

386
00:34:55,535 --> 00:34:57,705
Aren't we just driving home?

387
00:34:59,455 --> 00:35:00,455
Well, yeah.

388
00:35:03,075 --> 00:35:04,285
This is totally normal.

389
00:35:05,055 --> 00:35:07,115
This is how I wear my perfume.

390
00:35:07,375 --> 00:35:08,615
Mm...

391
00:35:08,805 --> 00:35:09,805
Okay.

392
00:35:19,525 --> 00:35:20,525
Hey,

393
00:35:23,185 --> 00:35:24,615
wanna go for a meal first?

394
00:35:27,715 --> 00:35:30,855
Well, I picked you up because I was planning to take you out for a meal.

395
00:35:30,895 --> 00:35:31,605
What?

396
00:35:32,155 --> 00:35:33,035
You're just...

397
00:35:33,285 --> 00:35:34,445
Are you teasing me?

398
00:35:35,535 --> 00:35:36,805
Don't tell me

399
00:35:37,135 --> 00:35:39,265
that you put on lipstick and wear your perfume,

400
00:35:39,345 --> 00:35:41,105
thinking I was asking you out on a date?

401
00:35:42,585 --> 00:35:44,155
Is it just all in your head?

402
00:35:44,365 --> 00:35:45,335
I'm just...

403
00:35:45,795 --> 00:35:48,885
looking for a friend to drink with, that's all.

404
00:35:49,475 --> 00:35:50,415
So...

405
00:35:50,515 --> 00:35:52,705
are you just looking for someone to give you a free ride

406
00:35:52,965 --> 00:35:56,125
and also take care of you while you're blackout drunk?

407
00:35:56,535 --> 00:35:57,535
Ugh,

408
00:35:58,105 --> 00:35:59,105
I'm not gonna get drunk anymore.

409
00:36:01,605 --> 00:36:02,375
Tonight,

410
00:36:02,645 --> 00:36:04,485
I'll show up as a hottie

411
00:36:04,565 --> 00:36:06,345
in case I can get someone to fall for me.

412
00:36:07,755 --> 00:36:08,545
Really now?

413
00:36:08,835 --> 00:36:09,705
Who?

414
00:36:14,855 --> 00:36:15,585
Dunno.

415
00:36:16,505 --> 00:36:18,685
There's gotta be someone who thinks I'm gorgeous.

416
00:36:38,095 --> 00:36:39,675
Are you busy, Miss?

417
00:36:40,515 --> 00:36:41,515
Hey,

418
00:36:41,955 --> 00:36:43,705
I thought you said you were going to be done late?

419
00:36:44,535 --> 00:36:46,105
Well, I was done earlier than expected.

420
00:36:46,545 --> 00:36:48,025
That's why I could come see you.

421
00:36:49,825 --> 00:36:50,825
So, how is it going?

422
00:36:53,935 --> 00:36:56,505
I'm exhausted to the bone.

423
00:36:57,175 --> 00:37:00,355
I just realized how exhausting it is being an executive.

424
00:37:00,385 --> 00:37:01,385
Mm-hm.

425
00:37:02,825 --> 00:37:04,185
Can I charge my battery with you?

426
00:37:04,635 --> 00:37:06,205
Aw, getting so affectionate the second I got here?

427
00:37:09,755 --> 00:37:12,275
No cookies for you today, though.

428
00:37:14,215 --> 00:37:15,215
Jeez, you...

429
00:37:16,165 --> 00:37:17,715
I have something for you.

430
00:37:19,115 --> 00:37:20,355
What is it?

431
00:37:20,525 --> 00:37:22,395
Now this is exciting.

432
00:37:28,505 --> 00:37:29,555
Here you go.

433
00:37:33,345 --> 00:37:35,125
Hey!

434
00:37:37,615 --> 00:37:39,815
I forgot about this photo entirely.

435
00:37:41,325 --> 00:37:42,685
Do you like it?

436
00:37:44,755 --> 00:37:46,275
I like that you were the one who took it.

437
00:37:46,355 --> 00:37:49,325
But my face? I look so dumbfounded.

438
00:37:49,705 --> 00:37:51,205
You don't!

439
00:37:51,335 --> 00:37:52,865
You look extremely cute.

440
00:37:54,215 --> 00:37:57,385
You know, I love this photo so much...

441
00:37:59,855 --> 00:38:02,425
because it was the very first photo I've taken of you.

442
00:38:05,925 --> 00:38:07,325
It's hard to believe

443
00:38:08,655 --> 00:38:10,675
that this photo

444
00:38:11,135 --> 00:38:13,305
brought us all the way here.

445
00:38:15,875 --> 00:38:18,945
In hindsight, that was such a fun day.

446
00:38:20,625 --> 00:38:21,945
The spark in my eyes...

447
00:38:22,335 --> 00:38:25,145
You could tell from a different planet that I was into you.

448
00:38:28,645 --> 00:38:31,405
If you'd taken a photo of me that day, it would've been nice.

449
00:38:33,775 --> 00:38:36,455
That way, you can see the sparks in my eyes,

450
00:38:36,685 --> 00:38:38,145
screaming that I was into you, too.

451
00:38:41,035 --> 00:38:42,925
What about the sparks in your eyes now?

452
00:38:45,355 --> 00:38:46,505
Don't you see it?

453
00:38:49,905 --> 00:38:50,755
Nope.

454
00:38:56,585 --> 00:38:57,875
Do you see it now?

455
00:39:02,005 --> 00:39:03,605
So clearly.

456
00:39:03,825 --> 00:39:05,365
Couldn't be clearer.

457
00:39:08,015 --> 00:39:14,045
♫Let me hold you close, don't let go tonight,♫

458
00:39:17,435 --> 00:39:19,045
You've fully charged my battery.

459
00:39:19,485 --> 00:39:21,965
I'm motivated to keep working now.

460
00:39:22,885 --> 00:39:24,965
Okay. How much work do you have left?

461
00:39:25,125 --> 00:39:26,245
I'll help.

462
00:39:27,215 --> 00:39:28,875
Quite a bit left.

463
00:39:29,105 --> 00:39:30,515
I have something to sign, and...

464
00:39:30,825 --> 00:39:32,285
I have to read this stack.

465
00:39:33,195 --> 00:39:34,115
Let me see.

466
00:39:34,145 --> 00:39:36,245
Hold up. Let me place this down.

467
00:39:38,625 --> 00:39:40,735
You did a beautiful job there.

468
00:39:41,635 --> 00:39:42,475
Of course.

469
00:39:42,675 --> 00:39:44,065
My girl is beautiful, after all.

470
00:39:45,625 --> 00:39:51,915
♫Let me hold you close, don't let go tonight,♫

471
00:39:52,015 --> 00:39:58,635
♫Come a little closer and hear my heart inside♫

472
00:39:59,325 --> 00:40:04,935
♫Every beat is whispering all I feel for you,♫

473
00:40:04,985 --> 00:40:11,625
♫No more hiding, yes, it's true, would you be mine?♫

474
00:40:18,005 --> 00:40:19,315
All this time,

475
00:40:19,465 --> 00:40:22,905
W Empire has delivered the best projects in many areas.

476
00:40:24,205 --> 00:40:26,435
But it will be different this time.

477
00:40:26,945 --> 00:40:29,235
Not only is real estate about constructing a building,

478
00:40:29,635 --> 00:40:32,255
but also about determining how people will live their lives.

479
00:40:35,315 --> 00:40:37,245
Therefore, I've decided that

480
00:40:37,755 --> 00:40:40,935
we will build W Empire's own area.

481
00:40:44,865 --> 00:40:47,365
But this project requires such a high investment.

482
00:40:47,585 --> 00:40:49,485
We're risking the entirety of our portfolio.

483
00:40:52,225 --> 00:40:54,015
If we just own the land,

484
00:40:54,125 --> 00:40:55,905
all we can be is landowners.

485
00:40:56,585 --> 00:40:59,275
But if we manage the whole ecosystem,

486
00:40:59,545 --> 00:41:02,395
we will be the price setter for the whole area.

487
00:41:04,265 --> 00:41:07,385
Others buy land and wait for its value to increase,

488
00:41:07,895 --> 00:41:12,085
but W Empire will create its value from day one.

489
00:41:17,015 --> 00:41:18,075
Okay,

490
00:41:18,115 --> 00:41:20,215
let's see this project through, then.

491
00:41:21,745 --> 00:41:23,055
Let's get started.

492
00:42:13,318 --> 00:42:14,318
It's a shame, right?

493
00:42:16,409 --> 00:42:18,519
That we don't get to spend more time with our kids.

494
00:42:20,919 --> 00:42:22,929
But I'm happy to see them happy.

495
00:42:25,229 --> 00:42:27,639
Isn't that what we want?

496
00:42:29,389 --> 00:42:31,089
For them to live their own life

497
00:42:32,789 --> 00:42:34,089
without having to do things for us?

498
00:42:39,269 --> 00:42:40,139
Right now,

499
00:42:41,769 --> 00:42:44,529
it's time we live for ourselves.

500
00:42:52,229 --> 00:42:53,569
While I disappeared,

501
00:42:56,989 --> 00:42:58,669
I barely remembered

502
00:42:59,319 --> 00:43:00,899
what my goals in life were.

503
00:43:04,989 --> 00:43:07,279
I just breathed through the days,

504
00:43:07,999 --> 00:43:10,469
waiting to be reunited with her.

505
00:43:17,472 --> 00:43:19,782
Right now, you're also just living through the days,

506
00:43:19,982 --> 00:43:21,422
except you're with me.

507
00:43:23,932 --> 00:43:24,652
Hey,

508
00:43:25,259 --> 00:43:27,619
can we not talk about the past anymore?

509
00:43:28,559 --> 00:43:31,169
Let's talk about today, tomorrow,

510
00:43:31,739 --> 00:43:33,929
what we will be doing today,

511
00:43:34,353 --> 00:43:35,653
what we will be eating,

512
00:43:36,016 --> 00:43:37,256
where we will go out to,

513
00:43:37,326 --> 00:43:38,986
or what songs we will listen to.

514
00:43:39,276 --> 00:43:41,416
These are the only topics we will be discussing.

515
00:43:44,756 --> 00:43:47,006
I see that you still boss people around.

516
00:43:48,966 --> 00:43:50,366
But you do know

517
00:43:51,916 --> 00:43:54,066
that I don't obey easily, don't you?

518
00:43:56,786 --> 00:43:57,886
I sure do.

519
00:43:59,106 --> 00:44:00,436
That's why we're together.

520
00:44:02,836 --> 00:44:04,596
And we'll be together for a long time.

521
00:44:14,156 --> 00:44:15,066
Have you ever thought...

522
00:44:17,026 --> 00:44:18,536
that if you could turn back time,

523
00:44:19,316 --> 00:44:20,766
what would you fix?

524
00:44:21,286 --> 00:44:22,656
This again!

525
00:44:23,236 --> 00:44:25,156
I asked you not to talk about the past,

526
00:44:25,186 --> 00:44:27,056
and you still want to.

527
00:44:27,096 --> 00:44:29,196
Well, I'm curious!

528
00:44:29,306 --> 00:44:30,766
It's just curiosity!

529
00:44:30,796 --> 00:44:32,046
Okay, okay.

530
00:44:32,556 --> 00:44:35,406
If I could turn back time...

531
00:44:35,436 --> 00:44:36,436
Mm-hm.

532
00:44:56,566 --> 00:44:58,156
If I could turn back time,

533
00:45:01,596 --> 00:45:04,556
I would never let you run away by yourself.

534
00:45:27,616 --> 00:45:29,006
Thank you.

535
00:45:45,756 --> 00:45:49,756
♫Never a second could I forget you♫

536
00:45:49,786 --> 00:45:53,546
♫You're still here when night comes through♫

537
00:45:53,576 --> 00:45:58,046
♫I don't wish to wake up sometimes,♫

538
00:45:58,076 --> 00:46:01,346
♫Afraid that you'd say goodbye♫

539
00:46:01,436 --> 00:46:04,966
♫I dream of another rendezvous♫

540
00:46:05,006 --> 00:46:12,916
♫To say that I'll never stop missing you♫

541
00:47:24,816 --> 00:47:25,616
Hey,

542
00:47:26,266 --> 00:47:27,926
when you said you weren't scared,

543
00:47:27,956 --> 00:47:30,346
I didn't think you'd be this daring.

544
00:47:32,716 --> 00:47:33,676
How about that?

545
00:47:33,866 --> 00:47:35,316
Haven't I made it so far

546
00:47:35,536 --> 00:47:39,376
from someone who was on the verge of puking in your passenger seat?

547
00:47:40,116 --> 00:47:41,106
You have.

548
00:47:41,266 --> 00:47:42,316
You've come so far.

549
00:47:44,076 --> 00:47:46,116
I've only understood

550
00:47:46,146 --> 00:47:49,306
how you can let out your anger by driving really fast.

551
00:47:50,196 --> 00:47:51,646
Mm, yeah.

552
00:47:52,326 --> 00:47:53,326
Well, what are you angry about?

553
00:47:53,596 --> 00:47:54,796
What's there to be angry about?

554
00:47:55,486 --> 00:47:56,576
Tons.

555
00:47:57,086 --> 00:47:58,086
For example,

556
00:47:59,486 --> 00:48:01,246
you take your time picking up my phone.

557
00:48:01,386 --> 00:48:02,636
You don't reply to my texts...

558
00:48:02,676 --> 00:48:03,196
Uh-huh...

559
00:48:03,226 --> 00:48:04,816
You fall asleep before I do.

560
00:48:05,026 --> 00:48:06,746
You don't wake me up in the morning.

561
00:48:06,836 --> 00:48:07,896
You don't wish me a goodnight.

562
00:48:07,936 --> 00:48:10,006
And you don't wish me a good morning.

563
00:48:10,716 --> 00:48:11,716
Are you really angry?

564
00:48:12,546 --> 00:48:13,546
Over those things?

565
00:48:13,646 --> 00:48:14,336
Mm.

566
00:48:14,456 --> 00:48:15,866
Come on, let me see your angry face.

567
00:48:18,046 --> 00:48:18,886
Angrier.

568
00:48:20,656 --> 00:48:21,726
Even angrier!

569
00:48:21,936 --> 00:48:24,556
Ugh, you! Why do I need to be angry?

570
00:48:26,176 --> 00:48:27,256
Nope,

571
00:48:27,496 --> 00:48:28,866
I'm not gonna let you be angry.

572
00:48:28,976 --> 00:48:30,096
From now on,

573
00:48:30,126 --> 00:48:32,736
I'll give in to all of your demands.

574
00:48:36,216 --> 00:48:38,716
Just as long as our lives

575
00:48:39,506 --> 00:48:41,276
are surrounded by happiness

576
00:48:41,646 --> 00:48:44,336
and smiles every day.

577
00:48:45,425 --> 00:48:46,945
All this time,

578
00:48:48,375 --> 00:48:49,935
I was sad,

579
00:48:50,005 --> 00:48:53,375
crying so much I could fill an ocean.

580
00:48:54,856 --> 00:48:55,856
Of course.

581
00:48:56,665 --> 00:48:59,675
From now on, I'll make sure you're nothing but smiley.

582
00:48:59,805 --> 00:49:00,555
Come on.

583
00:49:00,745 --> 00:49:02,705
Wouldn't you show me your smile?

584
00:49:03,555 --> 00:49:05,175
I'm smiley enough, dear.

585
00:49:05,485 --> 00:49:06,255
Smile.

586
00:49:06,335 --> 00:49:07,155
I am smiling.

587
00:49:08,065 --> 00:49:12,425
This was the very smile that impressed me from the night we met.

588
00:49:14,725 --> 00:49:18,015
If it wasn't for me already having proposed,

589
00:49:18,629 --> 00:49:20,319
with this vibe...

590
00:49:21,705 --> 00:49:23,625
I would've asked you to marry me all over again.

591
00:49:25,412 --> 00:49:26,612
Ask me, then.

592
00:49:27,045 --> 00:49:28,065
Go on.

593
00:49:28,708 --> 00:49:31,148
When you proposed before, there were so many dramas around it.

594
00:49:31,205 --> 00:49:33,075
I bet it wasn't auspicious.

595
00:49:33,415 --> 00:49:34,415
Should we get married again?

596
00:49:36,789 --> 00:49:37,669
No.

597
00:49:38,815 --> 00:49:40,425
I don't want to get married again.

598
00:49:42,435 --> 00:49:46,075
All this time, through good times and bad,

599
00:49:46,335 --> 00:49:48,475
having you in my life

600
00:49:49,055 --> 00:49:51,315
has been the most beautiful thing.

601
00:49:54,645 --> 00:49:56,325
I don't need anything else.

602
00:50:00,532 --> 00:50:02,192
Thank you, Lalin,

603
00:50:03,163 --> 00:50:06,623
for rescuing me from loneliness.

604
00:50:08,135 --> 00:50:09,265
I told you

605
00:50:09,592 --> 00:50:13,442
that I'd be lonely with you from the first day we met.

606
00:50:14,652 --> 00:50:16,132
I finally did it.

607
00:50:19,432 --> 00:50:23,869
♫The one who stays by my side♫

608
00:50:24,106 --> 00:50:28,675
♫Through whatever days and nights♫

609
00:50:29,366 --> 00:50:31,615
♫I want to whisper by your ears,♫

610
00:50:31,635 --> 00:50:36,815
♫From now on, for many years,♫

611
00:50:37,335 --> 00:50:41,855
♫Hold on to my hands tightly♫

612
00:50:41,911 --> 00:50:46,391
♫Would you be here, right next to me?♫

613
00:50:46,445 --> 00:50:50,268
♫Look at me, tell me honestly♫

614
00:50:50,302 --> 00:50:53,383
♫If you feel as I do♫

615
